        [
          "Malkavian who believes God speaks to him in a loud, Roaring voice."
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Oliver/Olivia Frank: A Malkavian “True Believer.” Raised by a politician in the best areas of Los Angeles, their every move was watched and corrected, lest they ruin the family’s “good image.” They were taken to church from a young age as it was considered a very In thing to do at the time, until they were sent off to a Christian boarding school “for their own good.” What followed was a life of quiet contemplation and study, their only outlet being the athletics and boxing programs they had been enrolled in. When they were able to take part in Church outreach programs, they did so with Gusto, happy to pitch in to help their fellow man. A stint in the military followed their education, (Again, it was good for their public image,) but that did nothing to hamper their faith. And indeed, their faith was their greatest comfort through the embrace, when a Malkavian whose thirst for innocence knew no bounds decided to prove that even the most religious man could be corrupted with the Blood of Caine. But, little did they know their attempts only strengthened their faith, and indeed, brought them even closer to God. Now He speaks to them in a loud, roaring voice. God tells them truths, and has revealed that the Cainite’s are truly the chosen of God, and dictates his will, brooking little argument. His first commandment was to kill the Foul Beast that was their sire. Currently He has told them that the Devil has taken up residence in Los Angeles, and that he must be rooted out if the Chosen are to survive. There are some here who know where the Adversary dwells, and the devil will be found, cast out of the City, and if They can Save a few souls along the way? Then so be it."
        ],
